ASER shall for each FY prepare detailed annual work plan and operating budget. The draft annual work program and budget documentsubmitted to IDA for its review no later than 2 months before FY.
ASER shall implement Parts A of the Project in accordance with the guidelines, procedures, timetable and other specifications setforth in the ESMF and the RPF.
ASER shall maintain (except with prior approval of IDA) its main management comprising the General Director, Director of the DFER,Accountant, a Procurement Specialist and a specialist in concess

The Borrower has adopted the Project Implementation Manual, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association.
The Borrower shall ensure that all records (contracts, orders, invoices, bills, receiptsand other documents) evidencingexpenditures are retained until at least one year after the Audit
The Borrower shall ensure that the principles and adjustment mechanisms oftariffs for electric services in rural areas shall notbe modified without prior approval ofthe Association.
The Borrower shall establish and maintain a financial management system, including records and accounts, and prepare financialstatements, acceptable to IDA.
The Borrower shall furnish to the Association not later than six months after the end of each year, (A) certified copies of thefinancial statements and (B) an opinion by auditors.
The Borrower shall have the financial statements referred to in paragraph (a) of this Section for each fiscal year (or otherperiodagreed to by the Association), audited, acceptable to IDA.
The Borrower shall prepare andfurnish to the Association a financial monitoring report, in form and substancesatisfactory to theAssociation

title.narrative: Reduce net CO2 emissions and promote conservation by encouraging use of renewable sources of energy, efficient lamps and improved cookstoves, improved carbonisation methods and improved woodfuel stove

baseline.value: No renewable energy based capacity installed by the project. No LBC installed yet.

comment.narrative: Installed capacity in renewable energy based systems (Measured in W or Wp); Number of highly efficient lamps; Green house gasesemissions avoided .
The full implementation of the project will significantly exceed the objectives.

As of August 2012 six (6) concessions were awarded, including two (2) from IDA financing. The implementation of the full programthrough concessions, ERILs (village based concessions), multisectoral projects (PREMS) by all donors financing will allow aninstall capacity of 4.1 MWc through solar systems as follows: by end of 2012, 1.1 MWc). The full implementation of the program willenable the installation of 610065 efficient lamps. This will result in a reduction of CO2 emissions of 38 000 metric tons. This hasresulted in a CDM project . Two contracts of CO2 purchase have been signed with CDCF and UCFT2 for an amount of 235 000 tones ofC02. For theconcessions and ERILs an EMF was validated by the Direction of Environment.
